OL,3,CBereaved parents 'not alone' as
OL,4,Cremembrance weekend held at hospital
OL,6,FThe event happens on the first weekend
OL,7,Fin December every year, and is open to
OL,8,Fanyone who has lost a child during
OL,9,Fpregnancy, birth or childhood.
OL,11,FCeri Morris, a senior midwife at the
OL,12,Fhospital, said: "What we've found over
OL,13,Fthe years is that when we bring people
OL,14,Ftogether to do crafting they talk
OL,15,Fbetter when they're side by side.
OL,17,F"It's really nice that people
OL,18,Funderstand that our care that we give
OL,19,Fdoesn't just end when we discharge
OL,20,Fthem. We're still remembering you and
OL,21,Fyour loss."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
